Cold but worth it!

fields.description: A historic surf region in Europe with a variety of breaks and stunning scenery.

fields.name: Jeffrey’s Bay
fields.description: One of the world's most famous right-hand point breaks, offering long and perfect waves.

fields.name: Taghazout
fields.description: A charming surf village in Morocco, known for its consistent right-hand point breaks.

fields.name: Cloudbreak
fields.description: World-renowned surf break with challenging waves for experienced surfers.

fields.name: Shonan Kamakura
fields.description: A well-known surf spot near Tokyo with consistent waves.

fields.name: Mentawai
fields.description: A tropical paradise offering world-class waves on remote islands.

fields.name: Popoyo
fields.description: A quiet surf destination in Nicaragua, offering consistent surf and relaxed vibes.

fields.name: Hossegor
fields.description: A famous surf town in southwest France with powerful beach breaks.

fields.name: Nazare
fields.description: Famous for its record-breaking big waves, attracting the world's best surfers.

fields.name: Gold Coast
fields.description: A popular surf destination with excellent waves and vibrant city life.

fields.name: Florianopolis
fields.description: Known for its beautiful beaches and consistent surf spots.

fields.name: Oahu North Shore
fields.description:
World-class surf destination with massive winter swells.
The proving ground for every surfers...

fields.name: Punta de Lobos
fields.description: One of Chile's best surf spots, famous for its left-hand point break.

fields.name: Raglan
fields.description: A famous surf destination in New Zealand with long left-hand point breaks.

fields.name: North Male Atolls
fields.description:
A stunning tropical surf destination with pristine waves.
Not as heavy as Indonesia but still some good barels...

fields.name: Bali Bukit Peninsula
fields.description: One of the best surf spots in Bali, known for its iconic left-hand reef break.

fields.name: El Tunco
fields.description: A small surf village with consistent right-hand point breaks.

fields.name: Kugenuma Beach
fields.description: Kugenuma Beach is known for its vibrant surfing community and consistent waves, making it ideal for beginners and intermediate surfers. It’s especially good during summer swells.

fields.name: Outer Reef Popoyo
fields.description: Outer Reef Popoyo is a heavy, powerful wave breaking on larger swells. It is recommended for expert surfers seeking big wave thrills. This wave can produce long, hollow barrels when conditions align.

fields.name: Manu Bay
fields.description: Manu Bay is one of Raglan’s most famous surf spots, offering long, peeling left-hand waves that can provide rides up to 600 meters. Ideal for intermediate to advanced surfers.

fields.name: Boneyards
fields.description: Boneyards is a powerful and fast reef break that connects into Supertubes. It offers challenging waves for experienced surfers seeking high-performance rides.

fields.name: Macaronis
fields.description: Often described as the most fun wave in the world, Macaronis is a perfect left-hand reef break known for its playful, consistent waves. Suitable for various skill levels, it offers long rides and consistent barrels.

fields.name: Panorama Beach
fields.description: Panorama Beach offers fun beach break waves perfect for beginners. It's a great spot for learning to surf and has a relaxed atmosphere.

fields.name: Zicatela Beach
fields.description: Zicatela Beach is one of the most famous and challenging beach breaks in the world. Known as the 'Mexican Pipeline,' it delivers powerful, hollow waves with heavy shorebreaks, making it a favorite for advanced and professional surfers.

fields.name: Snapper Rocks
fields.description: Snapper Rocks is part of the Superbank, renowned for producing long, hollow right-handers. It's a high-performance wave, making it a hotspot for advanced surfers.

fields.name: Teahupoo
fields.description: Best, heaviest, craziest barrel in the world...

fields.name: La Nord
fields.description: La Nord is renowned for its big wave potential, attracting pro surfers from around the world. It works best on large swells and offers powerful, heavy waves.

fields.name: Supertubes
fields.description: Supertubes at Jeffreys Bay is one of the world's most famous right-hand point breaks, offering long, fast, and flawless waves that can provide rides up to 300 meters. It is best suited for advanced surfers due to its speed and power.

fields.name: Restaurant
fields.description: Restaurant is a high-performance left-hand reef break located near Cloudbreak. It offers fast, hollow waves over a shallow reef, making it ideal for intermediate to advanced surfers. Works best on a mid to high tide.

fields.name: La Gravière
fields.description: La Gravière is famous for its heavy, hollow barrels that can rival world-class reef breaks. It's best suited for experienced surfers seeking challenging, powerful waves.

fields.name: Les Culs Nus
fields.description: Les Culs Nus offers consistent beach break waves suitable for surfers of all levels. It's a popular spot due to its reliability and accessibility.

fields.name: Guéthary
fields.description: Guéthary is known for its powerful reef breaks and is a spot favored by experienced surfers seeking bigger waves. It offers scenic views and strong swells.

fields.name: La Côte des Basques
fields.description: La Côte des Basques is the birthplace of surfing in France, offering gentle waves ideal for beginners and longboarders. It’s a scenic spot with a relaxed atmosphere.

fields.name: Joaquina Beach
fields.description: Joaquina Beach is famous for its strong waves and frequent surf competitions. It offers multiple peaks and consistent surf, making it suitable for various skill levels.

fields.name: La Bocana
fields.description: La Bocana is a powerful left-hand river mouth break with fast and hollow waves. Due to its strong currents and rocky bottom, it’s recommended for advanced and professional surfers.

fields.name: Kirra
fields.description: Kirra is famous worldwide for its fast, barrelling right-hand waves. It’s considered one of the best point breaks globally, ideal for advanced and professional surfers.

fields.name: Praia Mole
fields.description: Praia Mole is a popular beach break in Florianópolis, offering consistent and powerful waves. It attracts both intermediate and advanced surfers, especially during the autumn and winter months.

fields.name: Sunset Beach
fields.description: Sunset Beach is a challenging wave known for its size and power. It’s one of the most iconic surf spots on the North Shore, attracting advanced surfers from around the globe.

fields.name: Avellanas
fields.description: Avellanas offers a variety of reef and beach breaks with great waves for intermediate and advanced surfers. The beautiful setting and lack of crowds make it a favorite among locals.

fields.name: Cloudbreak
fields.description: Cloudbreak is one of the most iconic and challenging surf spots in the world, offering long, fast, and powerful left-hand reef breaks. It’s known for its hollow waves and is best suited for experienced surfers.

fields.name: Padang Padang
fields.description: Often referred to as the 'Balinese Pipeline,' Padang Padang is famous for its hollow, fast left-hand barrels, ideal for experienced surfers.

fields.name: Balangan
fields.description: Balangan features long, mellow left-hand waves, making it suitable for intermediate to advanced surfers.

fields.name: Burleigh Heads
fields.description: Burleigh Heads is a classic right-hand point break offering long, clean rides. It’s suitable for intermediate to advanced surfers and is a favorite spot for locals.

fields.name: Sunzal
fields.description: Sunzal is a long right-hand point break with gentle, rolling waves, making it an excellent spot for beginners and intermediates. It works best on a low to mid tide with a southerly swell.

fields.name: Pipeline
fields.description: Pipeline is one of the most famous and dangerous waves in the world, offering powerful left-hand barrels that break over a shallow reef. This wave is best left to expert and professional surfers.

fields.name: Praia do Norte
fields.description: Praia do Norte in Nazaré is renowned for its record-breaking giant waves, attracting the world's best big wave surfers. The unique underwater canyon amplifies the swell, creating massive, powerful waves that require extreme skill and courage to surf.

fields.name: Lance’s Right
fields.description: Lance’s Right is a world-class right-hand reef break offering long rides with barreling sections. It is ideal for intermediate and advanced surfers.

fields.name: Uluwatu
fields.description: Uluwatu is renowned for its consistent and powerful reef breaks, offering long, barreling left-hand waves suitable for advanced surfers.

fields.name: Cokes
fields.description: Cokes, also known as Colas, is famous for its hollow right-hand barrels and powerful waves. It’s a world-class surf spot best suited for experienced surfers looking for thrilling rides.

fields.name: Taapuna
fields.description: Taapuna offers clean, consistent waves and is one of the more accessible reef breaks around Papeete.

fields.name: Sapinus
fields.description: Powerful, hollow left-hand reef break that produces heavy, barreling waves. Can be dangerous but rewarding.

fields.name: Grande Plage
fields.description: Grand Plage is a central beach break in Biarritz, providing consistent waves suitable for all levels, though it can get crowded during peak season.

fields.name: Chickens
fields.description: Chickens is a fast, long left-hand reef break known for its multiple sections and fun waves. It's a popular surf spot in the Maldives, offering long rides and ideal conditions during the southwest monsoon season.

fields.name: Shichirigahama Beach
fields.description: Shichirigahama Beach is a popular surf spot in Shonan Kamakura, offering consistent beach break waves suitable for beginners and intermediates. It's best during typhoon season.

fields.name: Hash Point
fields.description: Hash Point is a mellow right-hand point break located in the heart of Taghazout. It's a great wave for beginners and intermediates when the swell is small.

fields.name: Punta de Lobos
fields.description: Punta de Lobos is a world-class left-hand point break known for its long, powerful waves. It is one of the best big wave spots in South America and attracts advanced surfers from around the world.

fields.name: Rifles
fields.description: Rifles is a long, fast right-hand reef break known for offering some of the longest and most thrilling rides in the Mentawais. It is best suited for advanced surfers.

fields.name: Kandui Lefts
fields.description: Kandui Lefts is a challenging and fast left-hand reef break, offering long rides and powerful barrels. It’s recommended for advanced to pro surfers due to its demanding conditions.

fields.name: Playa Langosta
fields.description: Playa Langosta is a quieter beach break just south of Tamarindo, offering more powerful and faster waves. It's ideal for intermediate and advanced surfers looking for less crowded conditions.

fields.name: Waimea Bay
fields.description: Waimea Bay is a legendary big wave spot on Oahu’s North Shore, breaking only during massive swells. It’s reserved for the most skilled big wave surfers.

fields.name: Playa Tamarindo
fields.description: Playa Tamarindo is one of Costa Rica's most popular surf spots, offering consistent beach break waves perfect for beginners and intermediates. The town has a lively atmosphere and plenty of amenities for travelers.

fields.name: Tullan Strand
fields.description: Tullan Strand is a long beach break that provides waves for all skill levels. It’s a popular spot among beginners and intermediates, with consistent swells throughout autumn.

fields.name: Nias
fields.description: Nias is a legendary surf spot known for its long, powerful right-hand reef break. It provides consistent barrels and is one of the most famous waves in Indonesia.

fields.name: Papara
fields.description: Papara is a more beginner-friendly beach break, popular with locals and ideal for surf lessons or warmups.

fields.name: The Peak
fields.description: The Peak in Bundoran is Ireland's most famous wave, offering a world-class reef break with both left and right-handers. It is ideal for advanced surfers seeking powerful, hollow waves.

fields.name: Popoyo Main break
fields.description: Popoyo Main break is a consistent reef break offering both left and right-hand waves. It caters to various skill levels, making it one of the most popular surf spots in Nicaragua.

fields.name: Whale Bay
fields.description: Whale Bay is another iconic surf spot in Raglan, known for its long left-hand point break waves and stunning coastal scenery. It works best on a mid to high tide.

fields.name: Orofara
fields.description: Orofara is a scenic, lesser-known reef break that delivers great right-handers and a quieter lineup.

fields.name: Anchor Point
fields.description: Anchor Point is one of Morocco's most iconic right-hand point breaks, known for its long, powerful rides and consistent swells during winter. Best surfed on a low to mid tide.

fields.name: Bingin
fields.description: Bingin is a perfect left-hander known for its short but intense barrels, best at mid to high tide.
